cern.extjfx.chart

Class XYChartPane<X,Y>

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.layout.Region
          • cern.extjfx.chart.XYChartPane<X,Y>
  • Type Parameters:
    X - type of X values
    Y - type of Y values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Styleable, EventTarget

    public class XYChartPane<X,Y>
extends Region
    A pane for XYCharts that allows adding custom chart plugins and overlay different chart types. The basic usage of the pane is following: 
     
 NumericAxis xAxis = new NumericAxis();
 xAxis.setAnimated(false);

 NumericAxis yAxis = new NumericAxis();
 yAxis.setAnimated(false);
 yAxis.setAutoRangePadding(0.1);

 LineChart<Number, Number> lineChart = new LineChart<>(xAxis, yAxis);
 XYChartPane<Number, Number> chartPane = new XYChartPane<>(lineChart);
 chartPane.getPlugins().addAll(new Zoomer(), new Panner(), new DataPointTooltip<>());
    Note that certain plugin implementations such as Zoomer or Panner work properly only if both X and Y axis are instances of NumericAxis.

    The overlay charts can be added on top of the base chart: 

     
 ScatterChart<Number, Number> overlayChart1 = ...;
 ScatterChart<Number, Number> overlayChart2 = ...;
 chartPane.getOverlayCharts().addAll(overlayChart1, overlayChart2);
    Constraints concerning overlay charts:
    • Chart background and content fill is set to null (to make it transparent and to not intercept mouse events).
    • Grid lines, title and legend are hidden. The same applies to horizontal and vertical zero line.
    • The X axis opacity is set to 0 and the auto-ranging is set to false (to follow the range of the base chart).
    • The X axis lower and upper bound follow (are bound) to the bounds of the X axis of the base chart.
    • The commonYAxisProperty() can be used to configure a single (common) Y axis or independent axes for each chart. The Y axis side is respected for each overlay chart. If the commonYAxis property is value is true the Y axis range follows the range of the base chart's Y axis.
    • The title of individual charts added to the pane are set to null. Use titleProperty() instead.
    • Legends of individual charts are hidden and therefore setting their visibility or side will have no effect. Instead set legend's visibility and side using XYChartPane properties with the same names.

      • enableAxisAutoRanging

        public final void enableAxisAutoRanging()
        Enables auto-ranging property on both X and Y axis by calling enableXAxisAutoRanging() and enableYAxisAutoRanging().

      • enableXAxisAutoRanging

        public final void enableXAxisAutoRanging()
        Enables auto-ranging property on the base chart X axis. Note that overlay chart X axes should have always the auto-ranging property set to false as their range should follow the range of the base chart X axis.

      • enableYAxisAutoRanging

        public final void enableYAxisAutoRanging()
        Enables auto-ranging property on the base chart Y axis and possibly on overlay charts Y axes.
        If there are overlay charts added to the pane, their Y axis auto-ranging property is set to true only if commonYAxisProperty() is false. In other words if there is a single Y axis, the auto-ranging of all overlay chart Y axes should be disabled and follow the Y range of the base chart.
